21// Liftoff Frames.
22//
23// slot Frame
24// +--------------------+---------------------------
25// n+4 | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
26// n+3 | parameter n |
27// ... | ... |
28// 4 | parameter 1 | or parameter 2
29// 3 | parameter 0 | or parameter 1
30// 2 | (result address) | or parameter 0
31// -----+--------------------+---------------------------
32// 1 | return addr (ra) |
33// 0 | previous frame (fp)|
34// -----+--------------------+ <-- frame ptr (fp)
35// -1 | StackFrame::WASM |
36// -2 | instance |
37// -3 | feedback vector|
38// -----+--------------------+---------------------------
39// -4 | slot 0 | ^
40// -5 | slot 1 | |
41// | | Frame slots
42// | | |
43// | | v
44// | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
45// -----+--------------------+ <-- stack ptr (sp)
46//
47
48inline MemOperand GetStackSlot(int offset) { return MemOperand(fp, -offset); }
49
50inline MemOperand GetInstanceDataOperand() {
51 return GetStackSlot(WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kInstanceDataOffset);
52}
53
54template <typename T>
55inline MemOperand GetMemOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register addr,
56 Register offset, T offset_imm,
57 bool i64_offset = false, unsigned shift_amount = 0) {
58 if (offset != no_reg) {
59 if (!i64_offset) {
60 assm->Dext(kScratchReg, offset, 0, 32);
61 offset = kScratchReg;
62 }
63 if (shift_amount != 0) {
64 assm->Dlsa(kScratchReg, addr, offset, shift_amount);
65 } else {
66 assm->daddu(kScratchReg, offset, addr);
67 }
68 addr = kScratchReg;
69 }
70 if (is_int31(offset_imm)) {
71 int32_t offset_imm32 = static_cast<int32_t>(offset_imm);
72 return MemOperand(addr, offset_imm32);
73 } else {
74 assm->li(kScratchReg2, Operand(offset_imm));
75 assm->daddu(kScratchReg, addr, kScratchReg2);
76 return MemOperand(kScratchReg, 0);
77 }
78}

80inline void Load(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, MemOperand src,
81 ValueKind kind) {
82 switch (kind) {
83 case kI16:
84 assm->Lh(dst.gp(), src);
85 break;
86 case kI32:
87 assm->Lw(dst.gp(), src);
88 break;
89 case kI64:
90 case kRef:
91 case kRefNull:
92 case kRtt:
93 assm->Ld(dst.gp(), src);
94 break;
95 case kF32:
96 assm->Lwc1(dst.fp(), src);
97 break;
98 case kF64:
99 assm->Ldc1(dst.fp(), src);
100 break;
101 case kS128:
102 assm->ld_b(dst.fp().toW(), src);
103 break;
104 default:
105 UNREACHABLE();
106 }
107}
108
109inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, MemOperand dst, LiftoffRegister src,
110 ValueKind kind) {
111 switch (kind) {
112 case kI16:
113 assm->Ush(src.gp(), dst, t8);
114 break;
115 case kI32:
116 assm->Usw(src.gp(), dst);
117 break;
118 case kI64:
119 case kRefNull:
120 case kRef:
121 case kRtt:
122 assm->Usd(src.gp(), dst);
123 break;
124 case kF32:
125 assm->Uswc1(src.fp(), dst, t8);
126 break;
127 case kF64:
128 assm->Usdc1(src.fp(), dst, t8);
129 break;
130 case kS128:
131 assm->st_b(src.fp().toW(), dst);
132 break;
133 default:
134 UNREACHABLE();
135 }
136}
137
138inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register base, int32_t offset,
139 LiftoffRegister src, ValueKind kind) {
140 MemOperand dst(base, offset);
141 Store(assm, dst, src, kind);
142}
143
144inline void push(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
145 switch (kind) {
146 case kI32:
147 assm->daddiu(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize);
148 assm->sw(reg.gp(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
149 break;
150 case kI64:
151 case kRefNull:
152 case kRef:
153 case kRtt:
154 assm->push(reg.gp());
155 break;
156 case kF32:
157 assm->daddiu(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize);
158 assm->swc1(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
159 break;
160 case kF64:
161 assm->daddiu(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize);
162 assm->Sdc1(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
163 break;
164 case kS128:
165 assm->daddiu(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize * 2);
166 assm->st_b(reg.fp().toW(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
167 break;
168 default:
169 UNREACHABLE();
170 }
171}

173#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
174inline void ChangeEndiannessLoad(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
175 LoadType type, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
176 bool is_float = false;
177 LiftoffRegister tmp = dst;
178 switch (type.value()) {
179 case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
180 case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
181 case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
182 case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
183 // No need to change endianness for byte size.
184 return;
185 case LoadType::kF32Load:
186 is_float = true;
187 tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
188 assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprI32ReinterpretF32, tmp, dst);
189 [[fallthrough]];
190 case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
191 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapUnsigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 4);
192 break;
193 case LoadType::kI32Load:
194 case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
195 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 4);
196 break;
197 case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
198 case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
199 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 2);
200 break;
201 case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
202 case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
203 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapUnsigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 2);
204 break;
205 case LoadType::kF64Load:
206 is_float = true;
207 tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
208 assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprI64ReinterpretF64, tmp, dst);
209 [[fallthrough]];
210 case LoadType::kI64Load:
211 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 8);
212 break;
213 default:
214 UNREACHABLE();
215 }
216
217 if (is_float) {
218 switch (type.value()) {
219 case LoadType::kF32Load:
220 assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprF32ReinterpretI32, dst, tmp);
221 break;
222 case LoadType::kF64Load:
223 assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprF64ReinterpretI64, dst, tmp);
224 break;
225 default:
226 UNREACHABLE();
227 }
228 }
229}
230
231inline void ChangeEndiannessStore(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister src,
232 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
233 bool is_float = false;
234 LiftoffRegister tmp = src;
235 switch (type.value()) {
236 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
237 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
238 // No need to change endianness for byte size.
239 return;
240 case StoreType::kF32Store:
241 is_float = true;
242 tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
243 assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprI32ReinterpretF32, tmp, src);
244 [[fallthrough]];
245 case StoreType::kI32Store:
246 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 4);
247 break;
248 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
249 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 2);
250 break;
251 case StoreType::kF64Store:
252 is_float = true;
253 tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
254 assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprI64ReinterpretF64, tmp, src);
255 [[fallthrough]];
256 case StoreType::kI64Store:
257 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 8);
258 break;
259 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
260 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 4);
261 break;
262 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
263 assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 2);
264 break;
265 default:
266 UNREACHABLE();
267 }
268
269 if (is_float) {
270 switch (type.value()) {
271 case StoreType::kF32Store:
272 assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprF32ReinterpretI32, src, tmp);
273 break;
274 case StoreType::kF64Store:
275 assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprF64ReinterpretI64, src, tmp);
276 break;
277 default:
278 UNREACHABLE();
279 }
280 }
281}
282#endif // V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN

286int LiftoffAssembler::PrepareStackFrame() {
287 int offset = pc_offset();
288 // When the frame size is bigger than 4KB, we need seven instructions for
289 // stack checking, so we reserve space for this case.
290 daddiu(sp, sp, 0);
291 nop();
292 nop();
293 nop();
294 nop();
295 nop();
296 nop();
297 return offset;
298}
299
300void LiftoffAssembler::CallFrameSetupStub(int declared_function_index) {
301// The standard library used by gcc tryjobs does not consider `std::find` to be
302// `constexpr`, so wrap it in a `#ifdef __clang__` block.
303#ifdef __clang__
304 static_assert(std::find(std::begin(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
305 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
306 kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg) ==
307 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
308#endif
309
310 // On MIPS64, we must push at least {ra} before calling the stub, otherwise
311 // it would get clobbered with no possibility to recover it. So just set
312 // up the frame here.
313 EnterFrame(StackFrame::WASM);
314 LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg),
315 WasmValue(declared_function_index));
316 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffFrameSetup);
317}
318
319void LiftoffAssembler::PrepareTailCall(int num_callee_stack_params,
320 int stack_param_delta) {
321 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
322 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
323
324 // Push the return address and frame pointer to complete the stack frame.
325 Ld(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 8));
326 Push(scratch);
327 Ld(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 0));
328 Push(scratch);
329
330 // Shift the whole frame upwards.
331 int slot_count = num_callee_stack_params + 2;
332 for (int i = slot_count - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
333 Ld(scratch, MemOperand(sp, i * 8));
334 Sd(scratch, MemOperand(fp, (i - stack_param_delta) * 8));
335 }
336
337 // Set the new stack and frame pointer.
338 daddiu(sp, fp, -stack_param_delta * 8);
339 Pop(ra, fp);
340}

344void LiftoffAssembler::PatchPrepareStackFrame(
345 int offset, SafepointTableBuilder* safepoint_table_builder,
346 bool feedback_vector_slot, size_t stack_param_slots) {
347 // The frame_size includes the frame marker and the instance slot. Both are
348 // pushed as part of frame construction, so we don't need to allocate memory
349 // for them anymore.
350 int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
351 // The frame setup builtin also pushes the feedback vector.
352 if (feedback_vector_slot) {
353 frame_size -= kSystemPointerSize;
354 }
355
356 // We can't run out of space, just pass anything big enough to not cause the
357 // assembler to try to grow the buffer.
358 constexpr int kAvailableSpace = 256;
359 MacroAssembler patching_assembler(
360 nullptr, AssemblerOptions{}, CodeObjectRequired::kNo,
361 ExternalAssemblerBuffer(buffer_start_ + offset, kAvailableSpace));
362
363 if (V8_LIKELY(frame_size < 4 * KB)) {
364 // This is the standard case for small frames: just subtract from SP and be
365 // done with it.
366 patching_assembler.Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_size));
367 return;
368 }
369
370 // The frame size is bigger than 4KB, so we might overflow the available stack
371 // space if we first allocate the frame and then do the stack check (we will
372 // need some remaining stack space for throwing the exception). That's why we
373 // check the available stack space before we allocate the frame. To do this we
374 // replace the {__ Daddu(sp, sp, -frame_size)} with a jump to OOL code that
375 // does this "extended stack check".
376 //
377 // The OOL code can simply be generated here with the normal assembler,
378 // because all other code generation, including OOL code, has already finished
379 // when {PatchPrepareStackFrame} is called. The function prologue then jumps
380 // to the current {pc_offset()} to execute the OOL code for allocating the
381 // large frame.
382 // Emit the unconditional branch in the function prologue (from {offset} to
383 // {pc_offset()}).
384
385 int imm32 = pc_offset() - offset - 3 * kInstrSize;
386 patching_assembler.BranchLong(imm32);
387
388 // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
389 // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
390 // check in the condition code.
391 RecordComment("OOL: stack check for large frame");
392 Label continuation;
393 if (frame_size < v8_flags.stack_size * 1024) {
394 Register stack_limit = kScratchReg;
395 LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
396 Daddu(stack_limit, stack_limit, Operand(frame_size));
397 Branch(&continuation, uge, sp, Operand(stack_limit));
398 }
399
400 Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
401 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
402 // The call will not return; just define an empty safepoint.
403 safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
404 if (v8_flags.debug_code) stop();
405
406 bind(&continuation);
407
408 // Now allocate the stack space. Note that this might do more than just
409 // decrementing the SP;
410 Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_size));
411
412 // Jump back to the start of the function, from {pc_offset()} to
413 // right after the reserved space for the {__ Daddu(sp, sp, -framesize)}
414 // (which is a Branch now).
415 int func_start_offset = offset + 7 * kInstrSize;
416 imm32 = func_start_offset - pc_offset() - 3 * kInstrSize;
417 BranchLong(imm32);
418}

442void LiftoffAssembler::CheckTierUp(int declared_func_index, int budget_used,
443 Label* ool_label,
444 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
445 Register budget_array = kScratchReg;
446
447 Register instance_data = cache_state_.cached_instance_data;
448 if (instance_data == no_reg) {
449 instance_data = budget_array; // Reuse the scratch register.
450 LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
451 }
452
453 constexpr int kArrayOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
454 WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTieringBudgetArrayOffset);
455 Ld(budget_array, MemOperand(instance_data, kArrayOffset));
456
457 int budget_arr_offset = kInt32Size * declared_func_index;
458
459 Register budget = kScratchReg2;
460 MemOperand budget_addr(budget_array, budget_arr_offset);
461 Lw(budget, budget_addr);
462 Subu(budget, budget, budget_used);
463 Sw(budget, budget_addr);
464
465 Branch(ool_label, less, budget, Operand(zero_reg));
466}

475void LiftoffAssembler::LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister reg, WasmValue value) {
476 switch (value.type().kind()) {
477 case kI32:
478 MacroAssembler::li(reg.gp(), Operand(value.to_i32()));
479 break;
480 case kI64:
481 MacroAssembler::li(reg.gp(), Operand(value.to_i64()));
482 break;
483 case kF32:
484 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f32_boxed().get_bits());
485 break;
486 case kF64:
487 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f64_boxed().get_bits());
488 break;
489 default:
490 UNREACHABLE();
491 }
492}

505void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFromInstance(Register dst, Register instance,
506 int offset, int size) {
507 DCHECK_LE(0, offset);
508 switch (size) {
509 case 1:
510 Lb(dst, MemOperand(instance, offset));
511 break;
512 case 4:
513 Lw(dst, MemOperand(instance, offset));
514 break;
515 case 8:
516 Ld(dst, MemOperand(instance, offset));
517 break;
518 default:
519 UNIMPLEMENTED();
520 }
521}

536void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTaggedPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
537 Register offset_reg,
538 int32_t offset_imm,
539 uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
540 bool needs_shift) {
541 static_assert(kTaggedSize == kInt64Size);
542 unsigned shift_amount = !needs_shift ? 0 : 3;
543 MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm,
544 false, shift_amount);
545 Ld(dst, src_op);
546
547 // Since LoadTaggedField might start with an instruction loading an immediate
548 // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_load_pc} after
549 // calling it.
550 if (protected_load_pc) {
551 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
552 }
553}
554
555void LiftoffAssembler::LoadProtectedPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
556 int32_t offset_imm) {
557 static_assert(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
558 LoadTaggedPointer(dst, src_addr, no_reg, offset_imm);
559}

561void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFullPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
562 int32_t offset_imm) {
563 MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, no_reg, offset_imm);
564 Ld(dst, src_op);
565}
566
567void LiftoffAssembler::StoreTaggedPointer(Register dst_addr,
568 Register offset_reg,
569 int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
570 LiftoffRegList pinned,
571 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
572 SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
573 static_assert(kTaggedSize == kInt64Size);
574 Register scratch = kScratchReg2;
575 MemOperand dst_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
576 Sd(src, dst_op);
577
578 // Since StoreTaggedField might start with an instruction loading an immediate
579 // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_load_pc} after
580 // calling it.
581 if (protected_store_pc) {
582 *protected_store_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
583 }
584
585 if (skip_write_barrier || v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
586
587 Label exit;
588 CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, scratch,
589 MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask, kZero, &exit);
590 JumpIfSmi(src, &exit);
591 CheckPageFlag(src, scratch, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask,
592 eq, &exit);
593 Daddu(scratch, dst_op.rm(), dst_op.offset());
594 CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(dst_addr, scratch, SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
595 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
596 bind(&exit);
597}
598
599void LiftoffAssembler::Load(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
600 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
601 LoadType type, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
602 bool is_load_mem, bool i64_offset,
603 bool needs_shift) {
604 unsigned shift_amount = needs_shift ? type.size_log_2() : 0;
605 MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm,
606 i64_offset, shift_amount);
607
608 switch (type.value()) {
609 case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
610 case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
611 Lbu(dst.gp(), src_op);
612 break;
613 case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
614 case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
615 Lb(dst.gp(), src_op);
616 break;
617 case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
618 case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
619 MacroAssembler::Ulhu(dst.gp(), src_op);
620 break;
621 case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
622 case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
623 MacroAssembler::Ulh(dst.gp(), src_op);
624 break;
625 case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
626 MacroAssembler::Ulwu(dst.gp(), src_op);
627 break;
628 case LoadType::kI32Load:
629 case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
630 MacroAssembler::Ulw(dst.gp(), src_op);
631 break;
632 case LoadType::kI64Load:
633 MacroAssembler::Uld(dst.gp(), src_op);
634 break;
635 case LoadType::kF32Load:
636 MacroAssembler::Ulwc1(dst.fp(), src_op, t8);
637 break;
638 case LoadType::kF32LoadF16:
639 UNIMPLEMENTED();
640 break;
641 case LoadType::kF64Load:
642 MacroAssembler::Uldc1(dst.fp(), src_op, t8);
643 break;
644 case LoadType::kS128Load:
645 MacroAssembler::ld_b(dst.fp().toW(), src_op);
646 break;
647 default:
648 UNREACHABLE();
649 }
650
651#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
652 if (is_load_mem) {
653 pinned.set(src_op.rm());
654 liftoff::ChangeEndiannessLoad(this, dst, type, pinned);
655 }
656#endif
657 // Since load macros might start with an instruction loading an immediate
658 // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_load_pc} after
659 // calling them.
660 if (protected_load_pc) {
661 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
662 }
663}
664
665void LiftoffAssembler::Store(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
666 uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
667 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
668 uint32_t* protected_store_pc, bool is_store_mem,
669 bool i64_offset) {
670 MemOperand dst_op =
671 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
672
673#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
674 if (is_store_mem) {
675 pinned.set(dst_op.rm());
676 LiftoffRegister tmp = kScratchReg2;
677 // Save original value.
678 Move(tmp, src, type.value_type());
679
680 src = tmp;
681 pinned.set(tmp);
682 liftoff::ChangeEndiannessStore(this, src, type, pinned);
683 }
684#endif
685
686 switch (type.value()) {
687 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
688 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
689 Sb(src.gp(), dst_op);
690 break;
691 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
692 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
693 MacroAssembler::Ush(src.gp(), dst_op, t8);
694 break;
695 case StoreType::kI32Store:
696 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
697 MacroAssembler::Usw(src.gp(), dst_op);
698 break;
699 case StoreType::kI64Store:
700 MacroAssembler::Usd(src.gp(), dst_op);
701 break;
702 case StoreType::kF32Store:
703 MacroAssembler::Uswc1(src.fp(), dst_op, t8);
704 break;
705 case StoreType::kF32StoreF16:
706 UNIMPLEMENTED();
707 break;
708 case StoreType::kF64Store:
709 MacroAssembler::Usdc1(src.fp(), dst_op, t8);
710 break;
711 case StoreType::kS128Store:
712 MacroAssembler::st_b(src.fp().toW(), dst_op);
713 break;
714 default:
715 UNREACHABLE();
716 }
717
718 // Since store macros might start with an instruction loading an immediate
719 // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_store_pc} after
720 // calling them.
721 if (protected_store_pc) {
722 *protected_store_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
723 }
724}
725
726void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoad(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
727 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
728 LoadType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
729 bool i64_offset) {
730 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
731 MemOperand src_op =
732 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
733 switch (type.value()) {
734 case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
735 case LoadType::kI64Load8U: {
736 Lbu(dst.gp(), src_op);
737 sync();
738 return;
739 }
740 case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
741 case LoadType::kI64Load16U: {
742 Lhu(dst.gp(), src_op);
743 sync();
744 return;
745 }
746 case LoadType::kI32Load: {
747 Lw(dst.gp(), src_op);
748 sync();
749 return;
750 }
751 case LoadType::kI64Load32U: {
752 Lwu(dst.gp(), src_op);
753 sync();
754 return;
755 }
756 case LoadType::kI64Load: {
757 Ld(dst.gp(), src_op);
758 sync();
759 return;
760 }
761 default:
762 UNREACHABLE();
763 }
764}
765
766void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicStore(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
767 uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
768 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
769 bool i64_offset) {
770 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
771 MemOperand dst_op =
772 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
773 switch (type.value()) {
774 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
775 case StoreType::kI32Store8: {
776 sync();
777 Sb(src.gp(), dst_op);
778 return;
779 }
780 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
781 case StoreType::kI32Store16: {
782 sync();
783 Sh(src.gp(), dst_op);
784 return;
785 }
786 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
787 case StoreType::kI32Store: {
788 sync();
789 Sw(src.gp(), dst_op);
790 return;
791 }
792 case StoreType::kI64Store: {
793 sync();
794 Sd(src.gp(), dst_op);
795 return;
796 }
797 default:
798 UNREACHABLE();
799 }
800}

802#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(load_linked, store_conditional, bin_instr) \
803 do { \
804 Label binop; \
805 sync(); \
806 bind(&binop); \
807 load_linked(result.gp(), MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
808 bin_instr(temp1, result.gp(), Operand(value.gp())); \
809 store_conditional(temp1, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
810 BranchShort(&binop, eq, temp1, Operand(zero_reg)); \
811 sync(); \
812 } while (0)
813
814#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(load_linked, store_conditional, size, \
815 bin_instr, aligned) \
816 do { \
817 Label binop; \
818 andi(temp3, temp0, aligned); \
819 Dsubu(temp0, temp0, Operand(temp3)); \
820 sll(temp3, temp3, 3); \
821 sync(); \
822 bind(&binop); \
823 load_linked(temp1, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
824 ExtractBits(result.gp(), temp1, temp3, size, false); \
825 bin_instr(temp2, result.gp(), value.gp()); \
826 InsertBits(temp1, temp2, temp3, size); \
827 store_conditional(temp1, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
828 BranchShort(&binop, eq, temp1, Operand(zero_reg)); \
829 sync(); \
830 } while (0)
831
832#define ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(name, inst32, inst64) \
833 void LiftoffAssembler::Atomic##name( \
834 Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm, \
835 LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result, StoreType type, \
836 bool i64_offset) { \
837 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value, result}; \
838 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg); \
839 Register temp0 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp(); \
840 Register temp1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp(); \
841 Register temp2 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp(); \
842 Register temp3 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp(); \
843 MemOperand dst_op = \
844 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset); \
845 Daddu(temp0, dst_op.rm(), dst_op.offset()); \
846 switch (type.value()) { \
847 case StoreType::kI64Store8: \
848 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Lld, Scd, 8, inst64, 7); \
849 break; \
850 case StoreType::kI32Store8: \
851 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll, Sc, 8, inst32, 3); \
852 break; \
853 case StoreType::kI64Store16: \
854 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Lld, Scd, 16, inst64, 7); \
855 break; \
856 case StoreType::kI32Store16: \
857 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll, Sc, 16, inst32, 3); \
858 break; \
859 case StoreType::kI64Store32: \
860 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Lld, Scd, 32, inst64, 7); \
861 break; \
862 case StoreType::kI32Store: \
863 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(Ll, Sc, inst32); \
864 break; \
865 case StoreType::kI64Store: \
866 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(Lld, Scd, inst64); \
867 break; \
868 default: \
869 UNREACHABLE(); \
870 } \
871 }
872
873ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Add, Addu, Daddu)
874ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Sub, Subu, Dsubu)
875ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(And, And, And)
876ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Or, Or, Or)
877ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Xor, Xor, Xor)
878#undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP
879#undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT
880#undef ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE

882#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(load_linked, store_conditional) \
883 do { \
884 Label exchange; \
885 sync(); \
886 bind(&exchange); \
887 load_linked(result.gp(), MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
888 mov(temp1, value.gp()); \
889 store_conditional(temp1, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
890 BranchShort(&exchange, eq, temp1, Operand(zero_reg)); \
891 sync(); \
892 } while (0)
893
894#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(load_linked, store_conditional, \
895 size, aligned) \
896 do { \
897 Label exchange; \
898 andi(temp1, temp0, aligned); \
899 Dsubu(temp0, temp0, Operand(temp1)); \
900 sll(temp1, temp1, 3); \
901 sync(); \
902 bind(&exchange); \
903 load_linked(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
904 ExtractBits(result.gp(), temp2, temp1, size, false); \
905 InsertBits(temp2, value.gp(), temp1, size); \
906 store_conditional(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
907 BranchShort(&exchange, eq, temp2, Operand(zero_reg)); \
908 sync(); \
909 } while (0)

911void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicExchange(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
912 uintptr_t offset_imm,
913 LiftoffRegister value,
914 LiftoffRegister result, StoreType type,
915 bool i64_offset) {
916 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value, result};
917 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
918 Register temp0 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
919 Register temp1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
920 Register temp2 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
921 MemOperand dst_op =
922 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
923 Daddu(temp0, dst_op.rm(), dst_op.offset());
924 switch (type.value()) {
925 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
926 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Lld, Scd, 8, 7);
927 break;
928 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
929 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll, Sc, 8, 3);
930 break;
931 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
932 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Lld, Scd, 16, 7);
933 break;
934 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
935 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll, Sc, 16, 3);
936 break;
937 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
938 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Lld, Scd, 32, 7);
939 break;
940 case StoreType::kI32Store:
941 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(Ll, Sc);
942 break;
943 case StoreType::kI64Store:
944 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(Lld, Scd);
945 break;
946 default:
947 UNREACHABLE();
948 }
949}
950#undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER
951#undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT
952
953#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(load_linked, \
954 store_conditional) \
955 do { \
956 Label compareExchange; \
957 Label exit; \
958 sync(); \
959 bind(&compareExchange); \
960 load_linked(result.gp(), MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
961 BranchShort(&exit, ne, expected.gp(), Operand(result.gp())); \
962 mov(temp2, new_value.gp()); \
963 store_conditional(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
964 BranchShort(&compareExchange, eq, temp2, Operand(zero_reg)); \
965 bind(&exit); \
966 sync(); \
967 } while (0)
968
969#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT( \
970 load_linked, store_conditional, size, aligned) \
971 do { \
972 Label compareExchange; \
973 Label exit; \
974 andi(temp1, temp0, aligned); \
975 Dsubu(temp0, temp0, Operand(temp1)); \
976 sll(temp1, temp1, 3); \
977 sync(); \
978 bind(&compareExchange); \
979 load_linked(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
980 ExtractBits(result.gp(), temp2, temp1, size, false); \
981 ExtractBits(temp2, expected.gp(), zero_reg, size, false); \
982 BranchShort(&exit, ne, temp2, Operand(result.gp())); \
983 InsertBits(temp2, new_value.gp(), temp1, size); \
984 store_conditional(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
985 BranchShort(&compareExchange, eq, temp2, Operand(zero_reg)); \
986 bind(&exit); \
987 sync(); \
988 } while (0)

990void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicCompareExchange(
991 Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
992 LiftoffRegister expected, LiftoffRegister new_value, LiftoffRegister result,
993 StoreType type, bool i64_offset) {
994 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, expected, new_value, result};
995 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
996 Register temp0 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
997 Register temp1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
998 Register temp2 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
999 MemOperand dst_op =
1000 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
1001 Daddu(temp0, dst_op.rm(), dst_op.offset());
1002 switch (type.value()) {
1003 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1004 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Lld, Scd, 8, 7);
1005 break;
1006 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1007 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll, Sc, 8, 3);
1008 break;
1009 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1010 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Lld, Scd, 16, 7);
1011 break;
1012 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1013 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll, Sc, 16, 3);
1014 break;
1015 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1016 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Lld, Scd, 32, 7);
1017 break;
1018 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1019 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(Ll, Sc);
1020 break;
1021 case StoreType::kI64Store:
1022 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(Lld, Scd);
1023 break;
1024 default:
1025 UNREACHABLE();
1026 }
1027}
1028#undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER
1029#undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT

1053void LiftoffAssembler::MoveStackValue(uint32_t dst_offset, uint32_t src_offset,
1054 ValueKind kind) {
1055 DCHECK_NE(dst_offset, src_offset);
1056 Register scratch = kScratchReg;
1057
1058 switch (kind) {
1059 case kI32:
1060 case kF32:
1061 Lw(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset));
1062 Sw(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset));
1063 break;
1064 case kI64:
1065 case kRefNull:
1066 case kRef:
1067 case kRtt:
1068 case kF64:
1069 Ld(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset));
1070 Sd(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset));
1071 break;
1072 case kS128:
1073 default:
1074 UNREACHABLE();
1075 }
1076}

1078void LiftoffAssembler::Move(Register dst, Register src, ValueKind kind) {
1079 DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1080 // TODO(ksreten): Handle different sizes here.
1081 MacroAssembler::Move(dst, src);
1082}
1083
1084void LiftoffAssembler::Move(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister src,
1085 ValueKind kind) {
1086 DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1087 if (kind != kS128) {
1088 MacroAssembler::Move(dst, src);
1089 } else {
1090 MacroAssembler::move_v(dst.toW(), src.toW());
1091 }
1092}

1094void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
1095 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1096 MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1097 switch (kind) {
1098 case kI32:
1099 Sw(reg.gp(), dst);
1100 break;
1101 case kI64:
1102 case kRef:
1103 case kRefNull:
1104 case kRtt:
1105 Sd(reg.gp(), dst);
1106 break;
1107 case kF32:
1108 Swc1(reg.fp(), dst);
1109 break;
1110 case kF64:
1111 MacroAssembler::Sdc1(reg.fp(), dst);
1112 break;
1113 case kS128:
1114 MacroAssembler::st_b(reg.fp().toW(), dst);
1115 break;
1116 default:
1117 UNREACHABLE();
1118 }
1119}
1120
1121void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, WasmValue value) {
1122 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1123 MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1124 switch (value.type().kind()) {
1125 case kI32: {
1126 MacroAssembler::li(kScratchReg, Operand(value.to_i32()));
1127 Sw(kScratchReg, dst);
1128 break;
1129 }
1130 case kI64:
1131 case kRef:
1132 case kRefNull: {
1133 MacroAssembler::li(kScratchReg, value.to_i64());
1134 Sd(kScratchReg, dst);
1135 break;
1136 }
1137 default:
1138 // kWasmF32 and kWasmF64 are unreachable, since those
1139 // constants are not tracked.
1140 UNREACHABLE();
1141 }
1142}
1143
1144void LiftoffAssembler::Fill(LiftoffRegister reg, int offset, ValueKind kind) {
1145 MemOperand src = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1146 switch (kind) {
1147 case kI32:
1148 Lw(reg.gp(), src);
1149 break;
1150 case kI64:
1151 case kRef:
1152 case kRefNull:
1153 Ld(reg.gp(), src);
1154 break;
1155 case kF32:
1156 Lwc1(reg.fp(), src);
1157 break;
1158 case kF64:
1159 MacroAssembler::Ldc1(reg.fp(), src);
1160 break;
1161 case kS128:
1162 MacroAssembler::ld_b(reg.fp().toW(), src);
1163 break;
1164 default:
1165 UNREACHABLE();
1166 }
1167}

1170 UNREACHABLE();
1171}
1172
1173void LiftoffAssembler::FillStackSlotsWithZero(int start, int size) {
1174 DCHECK_LT(0, size);
1175 RecordUsedSpillOffset(start + size);
1176
1177 if (size <= 12 * kStackSlotSize) {
1178 // Special straight-line code for up to 12 slots. Generates one
1179 // instruction per slot (<= 12 instructions total).
1180 uint32_t remainder = size;
1181 for (; remainder >= kStackSlotSize; remainder -= kStackSlotSize) {
1182 Sd(zero_reg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1183 }
1184 DCHECK(remainder == 4 || remainder == 0);
1185 if (remainder) {
1186 Sw(zero_reg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1187 }
1188 } else {
1189 // General case for bigger counts (12 instructions).
1190 // Use a0 for start address (inclusive), a1 for end address (exclusive).
1191 Push(a1, a0);
1192 Daddu(a0, fp, Operand(-start - size));
1193 Daddu(a1, fp, Operand(-start));
1194
1195 Label loop;
1196 bind(&loop);
1197 Sd(zero_reg, MemOperand(a0));
1198 daddiu(a0, a0, kSystemPointerSize);
1199 BranchShort(&loop, ne, a0, Operand(a1));
1200
1201 Pop(a1, a0);
1202 }
1203}

1207 Dsubu(dst, fp, Operand(offset));

1224void LiftoffAssembler::IncrementSmi(LiftoffRegister dst, int offset) {
1225 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1226 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1227 SmiUntag(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1228 Daddu(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
1229 SmiTag(scratch);
1230 Sd(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1231}

1236
1237void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divs(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1238 Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1239 Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1240 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap_div_by_zero, eq, rhs, Operand(zero_reg));
1241
1242 // Check if lhs == kMinInt and rhs == -1, since this case is unrepresentable.
1243 rotr(kScratchReg, lhs, 31);
1244 sltiu(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, 2);
1245 movn(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1246 addu(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg2, rhs);
1247 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap_div_unrepresentable, eq, kScratchReg2,
1248 Operand(zero_reg));
1249
1250 MacroAssembler::Div(dst, lhs, rhs);
1251}

1254 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1255 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap_div_by_zero, eq, rhs, Operand(zero_reg));
1256 MacroAssembler::Divu(dst, lhs, rhs);
1257}

1262 MacroAssembler::Mod(dst, lhs, rhs);
1263}
1264
1265void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_remu(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1266 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {

1269}

1344
1345void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_muli(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
1346 int32_t imm) {
1347 if (base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(imm)) {
1348 emit_i64_shli(dst, lhs, base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(imm));
1349 return;
1350 }
1351 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1352 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1353 MacroAssembler::li(scratch, Operand(imm));
1354 MacroAssembler::Dmul(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), scratch);
1355}
1356
1357bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_divs(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
1358 LiftoffRegister rhs,
1359 Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1360 Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1361 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap_div_by_zero, eq, rhs.gp(), Operand(zero_reg));
1362
1363 // Check if lhs == MinInt64 and rhs == -1, since this case is unrepresentable.
1364 drotr32(kScratchReg, lhs.gp(), 31);
1365 sltiu(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, 2);
1366 movn(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1367 daddu(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg2, rhs.gp());
1368 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap_div_unrepresentable, eq, kScratchReg2,
1369 Operand(zero_reg));
1370
1371 MacroAssembler::Ddiv(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), rhs.gp());
1372 return true;
1373}

1381}

1491
1492void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
1493 DoubleRegister rhs) {
1494 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1495 DoubleRegister scratch = rhs;
1496 if (dst == rhs) {
1497 scratch = kScratchDoubleReg;
1498 Move_d(scratch, rhs);
1499 }
1500 if (dst != lhs) {
1501 Move_d(dst, lhs);
1502 }
1503 binsli_w(dst.toW(), scratch.toW(), 0);
1504 } else {
1505 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1506 Register scratch1 = temps.Acquire();
1507 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
1508 mfc1(scratch1, lhs);
1509 mfc1(scratch2, rhs);
1510 srl(scratch2, scratch2, 31);
1511 Ins(scratch1, scratch2, 31, 1);
1512 mtc1(scratch1, dst);
1513 }
1514}

1520 Branch(&done);

1538void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
1539 DoubleRegister rhs) {
1540 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1541 DoubleRegister scratch = rhs;
1542 if (dst == rhs) {
1543 scratch = kScratchDoubleReg;
1544 Move_d(scratch, rhs);
1545 }
1546 if (dst != lhs) {
1547 Move_d(dst, lhs);
1548 }
1549 binsli_d(dst.toW(), scratch.toW(), 0);
1550 } else {
1551 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1552 Register scratch1 = temps.Acquire();
1553 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
1554 dmfc1(scratch1, lhs);
1555 dmfc1(scratch2, rhs);
1556 dsrl32(scratch2, scratch2, 31);
1557 Dins(scratch1, scratch2, 63, 1);
1558 dmtc1(scratch1, dst);
1559 }
1560}

1601
1602bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_type_conversion(WasmOpcode opcode,
1603 LiftoffRegister dst,
1604 LiftoffRegister src, Label* trap) {
1605 switch (opcode) {
1606 case kExprI32ConvertI64:
1607 MacroAssembler::Ext(dst.gp(), src.gp(), 0, 32);
1608 return true;
1609 case kExprI32SConvertF32: {
1610 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1611 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1612 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1613
1614 // Real conversion.
1615 MacroAssembler::Trunc_s_s(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1616 trunc_w_s(kScratchDoubleReg, rounded.fp());
1617 mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1618 // Avoid INT32_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT32_MIN instead,
1619 // because INT32_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1620 MacroAssembler::Addu(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1621 MacroAssembler::Slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, dst.gp());
1622 MacroAssembler::Movn(dst.gp(), kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1623
1624 // Checking if trap.
1625 mtc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1626 cvt_s_w(converted_back.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1627 MacroAssembler::CompareF32(EQ, rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp());
1628 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1629 return true;
1630 }
1631 case kExprI32UConvertF32: {
1632 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1633 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1634 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1635
1636 // Real conversion.
1637 MacroAssembler::Trunc_s_s(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1638 MacroAssembler::Trunc_uw_s(dst.gp(), rounded.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1639 // Avoid UINT32_MAX as an overflow indicator and use 0 instead,
1640 // because 0 allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1641 MacroAssembler::Addu(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1642 MacroAssembler::Movz(dst.gp(), zero_reg, kScratchReg);
1643
1644 // Checking if trap.
1645 MacroAssembler::Cvt_d_uw(converted_back.fp(), dst.gp());
1646 cvt_s_d(converted_back.fp(), converted_back.fp());
1647 MacroAssembler::CompareF32(EQ, rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp());
1648 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1649 return true;
1650 }
1651 case kExprI32SConvertF64: {
1652 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1653 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1654 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1655
1656 // Real conversion.
1657 MacroAssembler::Trunc_d_d(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1658 trunc_w_d(kScratchDoubleReg, rounded.fp());
1659 mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1660
1661 // Checking if trap.
1662 cvt_d_w(converted_back.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1663 MacroAssembler::CompareF64(EQ, rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp());
1664 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1665 return true;
1666 }
1667 case kExprI32UConvertF64: {
1668 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1669 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1670 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1671
1672 // Real conversion.
1673 MacroAssembler::Trunc_d_d(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1674 MacroAssembler::Trunc_uw_d(dst.gp(), rounded.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1675
1676 // Checking if trap.
1677 MacroAssembler::Cvt_d_uw(converted_back.fp(), dst.gp());
1678 MacroAssembler::CompareF64(EQ, rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp());
1679 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1680 return true;
1681 }
1682 case kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
1683 MacroAssembler::FmoveLow(dst.gp(), src.fp());
1684 return true;
1685 case kExprI64SConvertI32:
1686 sll(dst.gp(), src.gp(), 0);
1687 return true;
1688 case kExprI64UConvertI32:
1689 MacroAssembler::Dext(dst.gp(), src.gp(), 0, 32);
1690 return true;
1691 case kExprI64SConvertF32: {
1692 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1693 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1694 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1695
1696 // Real conversion.
1697 MacroAssembler::Trunc_s_s(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1698 trunc_l_s(kScratchDoubleReg, rounded.fp());
1699 dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1700 // Avoid INT64_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT64_MIN instead,
1701 // because INT64_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1702 MacroAssembler::Daddu(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1703 MacroAssembler::Slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, dst.gp());
1704 MacroAssembler::Movn(dst.gp(), kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1705
1706 // Checking if trap.
1707 dmtc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1708 cvt_s_l(converted_back.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1709 MacroAssembler::CompareF32(EQ, rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp());
1710 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1711 return true;
1712 }
1713 case kExprI64UConvertF32: {
1714 // Real conversion.
1715 MacroAssembler::Trunc_ul_s(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg,
1716 kScratchReg);
1717
1718 // Checking if trap.
1719 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap, eq, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
1720 return true;
1721 }
1722 case kExprI64SConvertF64: {
1723 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1724 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1725 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1726
1727 // Real conversion.
1728 MacroAssembler::Trunc_d_d(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1729 trunc_l_d(kScratchDoubleReg, rounded.fp());
1730 dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1731 // Avoid INT64_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT64_MIN instead,
1732 // because INT64_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1733 MacroAssembler::Daddu(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1734 MacroAssembler::Slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, dst.gp());
1735 MacroAssembler::Movn(dst.gp(), kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1736
1737 // Checking if trap.
1738 dmtc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1739 cvt_d_l(converted_back.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1740 MacroAssembler::CompareF64(EQ, rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp());
1741 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1742 return true;
1743 }
1744 case kExprI64UConvertF64: {
1745 // Real conversion.
1746 MacroAssembler::Trunc_ul_d(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg,
1747 kScratchReg);
1748
1749 // Checking if trap.
1750 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap, eq, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
1751 return true;
1752 }
1753 case kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
1754 dmfc1(dst.gp(), src.fp());
1755 return true;
1756 case kExprF32SConvertI32: {
1757 LiftoffRegister scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst});
1758 mtc1(src.gp(), scratch.fp());
1759 cvt_s_w(dst.fp(), scratch.fp());
1760 return true;
1761 }
1762 case kExprF32UConvertI32:
1763 MacroAssembler::Cvt_s_uw(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1764 return true;
1765 case kExprF32ConvertF64:
1766 cvt_s_d(dst.fp(), src.fp());
1767 return true;
1768 case kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
1769 MacroAssembler::FmoveLow(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1770 return true;
1771 case kExprF64SConvertI32: {
1772 LiftoffRegister scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst});
1773 mtc1(src.gp(), scratch.fp());
1774 cvt_d_w(dst.fp(), scratch.fp());
1775 return true;
1776 }
1777 case kExprF64UConvertI32:
1778 MacroAssembler::Cvt_d_uw(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1779 return true;
1780 case kExprF64ConvertF32:
1781 cvt_d_s(dst.fp(), src.fp());
1782 return true;
1783 case kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
1784 dmtc1(src.gp(), dst.fp());
1785 return true;
1786 case kExprI32SConvertSatF32: {
1787 // Other arches use round to zero here, so we follow.
1788 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1789 trunc_w_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1790 mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1791 } else {
1792 Label done;
1793 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1794 CompareIsNanF32(src.fp(), src.fp());
1795 BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1796 li(dst.gp(), static_cast<int32_t>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()));
1797 MacroAssembler::Move(
1798 kScratchDoubleReg,
1799 static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()));
1800 CompareF32(OLT, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1801 BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1802 trunc_w_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1803 mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1804 bind(&done);
1805 }
1806 return true;
1807 }
1808 case kExprI32UConvertSatF32: {
1809 Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1810 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1811 MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<float>(0.0));
1812 CompareF32(ULE, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1813 BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1814 Trunc_uw_s(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1815 bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1816 return true;
1817 }
1818 case kExprI32SConvertSatF64: {
1819 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1820 trunc_w_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1821 mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1822 } else {
1823 Label done;
1824 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1825 CompareIsNanF64(src.fp(), src.fp());
1826 BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1827 li(dst.gp(), static_cast<int32_t>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()));
1828 MacroAssembler::Move(
1829 kScratchDoubleReg,
1830 static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()));
1831 CompareF64(OLT, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1832 BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1833 trunc_w_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1834 mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1835 bind(&done);
1836 }
1837 return true;
1838 }
1839 case kExprI32UConvertSatF64: {
1840 Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1841 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1842 MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<double>(0.0));
1843 CompareF64(ULE, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1844 BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1845 Trunc_uw_d(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1846 bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1847 return true;
1848 }
1849 case kExprI64SConvertSatF32: {
1850 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1851 trunc_l_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1852 dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1853 } else {
1854 Label done;
1855 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1856 CompareIsNanF32(src.fp(), src.fp());
1857 BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1858 li(dst.gp(), static_cast<int64_t>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
1859 MacroAssembler::Move(
1860 kScratchDoubleReg,
1861 static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
1862 CompareF32(OLT, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1863 BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1864 trunc_l_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1865 dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1866 bind(&done);
1867 }
1868 return true;
1869 }
1870 case kExprI64UConvertSatF32: {
1871 Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1872 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1873 MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<float>(0.0));
1874 CompareF32(ULE, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1875 BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1876 Trunc_ul_s(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg, no_reg);
1877 bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1878 return true;
1879 }
1880 case kExprI64SConvertSatF64: {
1881 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1882 trunc_l_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1883 dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1884 } else {
1885 Label done;
1886 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1887 CompareIsNanF64(src.fp(), src.fp());
1888 BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1889 li(dst.gp(), static_cast<int64_t>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
1890 MacroAssembler::Move(
1891 kScratchDoubleReg,
1892 static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
1893 CompareF64(OLT, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1894 BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1895 trunc_l_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1896 dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1897 bind(&done);
1898 }
1899 return true;
1900 }
1901 case kExprI64UConvertSatF64: {
1902 Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1903 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1904 MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<double>(0.0));
1905 CompareF64(ULE, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1906 BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1907 Trunc_ul_d(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg, no_reg);
1908 bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1909 return true;
1910 }
1911 default:
1912 return false;
1913 }
1914}

1947void LiftoffAssembler::emit_cond_jump(Condition cond, Label* label,
1948 ValueKind kind, Register lhs,
1949 Register rhs,
1950 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
1951 if (rhs == no_reg) {
1952 DCHECK(kind == kI32 || kind == kI64);
1953 MacroAssembler::Branch(label, cond, lhs, Operand(zero_reg));
1954 } else {
1955 DCHECK((kind == kI32 || kind == kI64) ||
1956 (is_reference(kind) && (cond == kEqual || cond == kNotEqual)));
1957 MacroAssembler::Branch(label, cond, lhs, Operand(rhs));
1958 }
1959}

1993
1994inline FPUCondition ConditionToConditionCmpFPU(Condition condition,
1995 bool* predicate) {
1996 switch (condition) {
1997 case kEqual:
1998 *predicate = true;
1999 return EQ;
2000 case kNotEqual:
2001 *predicate = false;
2002 return EQ;
2003 case kUnsignedLessThan:
2004 *predicate = true;
2005 return OLT;
2006 case kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
2007 *predicate = false;
2008 return OLT;
2009 case kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
2010 *predicate = true;
2011 return OLE;
2012 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
2013 *predicate = false;
2014 return OLE;
2015 default:
2016 *predicate = true;
2017 break;
2018 }
2019 UNREACHABLE();
2020}
2021
2022inline void EmitAnyTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2023 LiftoffRegister src) {
2024 Label all_false;
2025 assm->BranchMSA(&all_false, MSA_BRANCH_V, all_zero, src.fp().toW(),
2026 USE_DELAY_SLOT);
2027 assm->li(dst.gp(), 0l);
2028 assm->li(dst.gp(), 1);
2029 assm->bind(&all_false);
2030}
2031
2032inline void EmitAllTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2033 LiftoffRegister src, MSABranchDF msa_branch_df) {
2034 Label all_true;
2035 assm->BranchMSA(&all_true, msa_branch_df, all_not_zero, src.fp().toW(),
2036 USE_DELAY_SLOT);
2037 assm->li(dst.gp(), 1);
2038 assm->li(dst.gp(), 0l);
2039 assm->bind(&all_true);
2040}
2041
2042inline void StoreToMemory(LiftoffAssembler* assm, MemOperand dst,
2043 const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src) {
2044 if (src.is_reg()) {
2045 Store(assm, dst, src.reg(), src.kind());
2046 return;
2047 }
2048
2049 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
2050 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
2051 if (src.is_const()) {
2052 if (src.i32_const() == 0) {
2053 temp = zero_reg;
2054 } else {
2055 assm->li(temp, src.i32_const());
2056 }
2057 } else {
2058 DCHECK(src.is_stack());
2059 if (value_kind_size(src.kind()) == 4) {
2060 assm->Lw(temp, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src.offset()));
2061 } else {
2062 assm->Ld(temp, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src.offset()));
2063 }
2064 }
2065
2066 if (value_kind_size(src.kind()) == 4) {
2067 assm->Sw(temp, dst);
2068 } else {
2069 DCHECK_EQ(8, value_kind_size(src.kind()));
2070 assm->Sd(temp, dst);
2071 }
2072}

2075
2076void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2077 DoubleRegister lhs,
2078 DoubleRegister rhs) {
2079 Label not_nan, cont;
2080 MacroAssembler::CompareIsNanF32(lhs, rhs);
2081 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(&not_nan);
2082 // If one of the operands is NaN, return 1 for f32.ne, else 0.
2083 if (cond == ne) {
2084 MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
2085 } else {
2086 MacroAssembler::Move(dst, zero_reg);
2087 }
2088 MacroAssembler::Branch(&cont);
2089
2090 bind(&not_nan);
2091
2092 MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
2093 bool predicate;
2094 FPUCondition fcond = liftoff::ConditionToConditionCmpFPU(cond, &predicate);
2095 MacroAssembler::CompareF32(fcond, lhs, rhs);
2096 if (predicate) {
2097 MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfNotFPUCondition(dst);
2098 } else {
2099 MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfFPUCondition(dst);
2100 }
2101
2102 bind(&cont);
2103}
2104
2105void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2106 DoubleRegister lhs,
2107 DoubleRegister rhs) {
2108 Label not_nan, cont;
2109 MacroAssembler::CompareIsNanF64(lhs, rhs);
2110 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(&not_nan);
2111 // If one of the operands is NaN, return 1 for f64.ne, else 0.
2112 if (cond == ne) {
2113 MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
2114 } else {
2115 MacroAssembler::Move(dst, zero_reg);
2116 }
2117 MacroAssembler::Branch(&cont);
2118
2119 bind(&not_nan);
2120
2121 MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
2122 bool predicate;
2123 FPUCondition fcond = liftoff::ConditionToConditionCmpFPU(cond, &predicate);
2124 MacroAssembler::CompareF64(fcond, lhs, rhs);
2125 if (predicate) {
2126 MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfNotFPUCondition(dst);
2127 } else {
2128 MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfFPUCondition(dst);
2129 }
2130
2131 bind(&cont);
2132}

2141void LiftoffAssembler::emit_smi_check(Register obj, Label* target,
2142 SmiCheckMode mode,
2143 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2144 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2145 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2146 And(scratch, obj, Operand(kSmiTagMask));
2147 Condition condition = mode == kJumpOnSmi ? eq : ne;
2148 Branch(target, condition, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
2149}

2151void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTransform(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
2152 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
2153 LoadType type,
2154 LoadTransformationKind transform,
2155 uint32_t* protected_load_pc) {
2156 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2157 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2158 MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
2159 MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
2160 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2161 MachineType memtype = type.mem_type();
2162
2163 if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend) {
2164 Ld(scratch, src_op);
2165 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2166 fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2167 clti_s_b(kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa, 0);
2168 ilvr_b(dst_msa, kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa);
2169 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
2170 xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
2171 fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2172 ilvr_b(dst_msa, kSimd128RegZero, dst_msa);
2173 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2174 fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2175 clti_s_h(kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa, 0);
2176 ilvr_h(dst_msa, kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa);
2177 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
2178 xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
2179 fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2180 ilvr_h(dst_msa, kSimd128RegZero, dst_msa);
2181 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2182 fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2183 clti_s_w(kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa, 0);
2184 ilvr_w(dst_msa, kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa);
2185 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
2186 xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
2187 fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2188 ilvr_w(dst_msa, kSimd128RegZero, dst_msa);
2189 }
2190 } else if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend) {
2191 xor_v(dst_msa, dst_msa, dst_msa);
2192 if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2193 Lwu(scratch, src_op);
2194 insert_w(dst_msa, 0, scratch);
2195 } else {
2196 DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), memtype);
2197 Ld(scratch, src_op);
2198 insert_d(dst_msa, 0, scratch);
2199 }
2200 } else {
2201 DCHECK_EQ(LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, transform);
2202 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2203 Lb(scratch, src_op);
2204 fill_b(dst_msa, scratch);
2205 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2206 Lh(scratch, src_op);
2207 fill_h(dst_msa, scratch);
2208 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2209 Lw(scratch, src_op);
2210 fill_w(dst_msa, scratch);
2211 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
2212 Ld(scratch, src_op);
2213 fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2214 }
2215 }
2216}

2241
2242void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_shuffle(LiftoffRegister dst,
2243 LiftoffRegister lhs,
2244 LiftoffRegister rhs,
2245 const uint8_t shuffle[16],
2246 bool is_swizzle) {
2247 MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
2248 MSARegister lhs_msa = lhs.fp().toW();
2249 MSARegister rhs_msa = rhs.fp().toW();
2250
2251 uint64_t control_hi = 0;
2252 uint64_t control_low = 0;
2253 for (int i = 7; i >= 0; i--) {
2254 control_hi <<= 8;
2255 control_hi |= shuffle[i + 8];
2256 control_low <<= 8;
2257 control_low |= shuffle[i];
2258 }
2259
2260 if (dst_msa == lhs_msa) {
2261 move_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, lhs_msa);
2262 lhs_msa = kSimd128ScratchReg;
2263 } else if (dst_msa == rhs_msa) {
2264 move_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, rhs_msa);
2265 rhs_msa = kSimd128ScratchReg;
2266 }
2267
2268 li(kScratchReg, control_low);
2269 insert_d(dst_msa, 0, kScratchReg);
2270 li(kScratchReg, control_hi);
2271 insert_d(dst_msa, 1, kScratchReg);
2272 vshf_b(dst_msa, rhs_msa, lhs_msa);
2273}
2274
2275void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_swizzle(LiftoffRegister dst,
2276 LiftoffRegister lhs,
2277 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2278 MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
2279 MSARegister lhs_msa = lhs.fp().toW();
2280 MSARegister rhs_msa = rhs.fp().toW();
2281
2282 if (dst == lhs) {
2283 move_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, lhs_msa);
2284 lhs_msa = kSimd128ScratchReg;
2285 }
2286 xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
2287 move_v(dst_msa, rhs_msa);
2288 vshf_b(dst_msa, kSimd128RegZero, lhs_msa);
2289}

2357#define SIMD_BINOP(name1, name2, type) \
2358 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_##name1##_extmul_low_##name2( \
2359 LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src1, LiftoffRegister src2) { \
2360 MacroAssembler::ExtMulLow(type, dst.fp().toW(), src1.fp().toW(), \
2361 src2.fp().toW()); \
2362 } \
2363 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_##name1##_extmul_high_##name2( \
2364 LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src1, LiftoffRegister src2) { \
2365 MacroAssembler::ExtMulHigh(type, dst.fp().toW(), src1.fp().toW(), \
2366 src2.fp().toW()); \
2367 }
2368
2369SIMD_BINOP(i16x8, i8x16_s, MSAS8)
2370SIMD_BINOP(i16x8, i8x16_u, MSAU8)
2371
2372SIMD_BINOP(i32x4, i16x8_s, MSAS16)
2373SIMD_BINOP(i32x4, i16x8_u, MSAU16)
2374
2375SIMD_BINOP(i64x2, i32x4_s, MSAS32)
2376SIMD_BINOP(i64x2, i32x4_u, MSAU32)
2377
2378#undef SIMD_BINOP
2379
2380#define SIMD_BINOP(name1, name2, type) \
2381 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_##name1##_extadd_pairwise_##name2( \
2382 LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) { \
2383 MacroAssembler::ExtAddPairwise(type, dst.fp().toW(), src.fp().toW()); \
2384 }

2390#undef SIMD_BINOP

2567void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_const(LiftoffRegister dst,
2568 const uint8_t imms[16]) {
2569 MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
2570 uint64_t vals[2];
2571 memcpy(vals, imms, sizeof(vals));
2572 li(kScratchReg, vals[0]);
2573 insert_d(dst_msa, 0, kScratchReg);
2574 li(kScratchReg, vals[1]);
2575 insert_d(dst_msa, 1, kScratchReg);
2576}

2598 LiftoffRegister lhs,
2599 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2600 nor_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, rhs.fp().toW(), rhs.fp().toW());

2603
2604void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_select(LiftoffRegister dst,
2605 LiftoffRegister src1,
2606 LiftoffRegister src2,
2607 LiftoffRegister mask) {
2608 if (dst == mask) {
2609 bsel_v(dst.fp().toW(), src2.fp().toW(), src1.fp().toW());
2610 } else {
2611 xor_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, src1.fp().toW(), src2.fp().toW());
2612 and_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg, mask.fp().toW());
2613 xor_v(dst.fp().toW(), kSimd128ScratchReg, src2.fp().toW());
2614 }
2615}

2633void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_bitmask(LiftoffRegister dst,
2634 LiftoffRegister src) {
2635 MSARegister scratch0 = kSimd128RegZero;
2636 MSARegister scratch1 = kSimd128ScratchReg;
2637 srli_b(scratch0, src.fp().toW(), 7);
2638 srli_h(scratch1, scratch0, 7);
2639 or_v(scratch0, scratch0, scratch1);
2640 srli_w(scratch1, scratch0, 14);
2641 or_v(scratch0, scratch0, scratch1);
2642 srli_d(scratch1, scratch0, 28);
2643 or_v(scratch0, scratch0, scratch1);
2644 shf_w(scratch1, scratch0, 0x0E);
2645 ilvev_b(scratch0, scratch1, scratch0);
2646 copy_u_h(dst.gp(), scratch0, 0);
2647}

3114void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_min(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3115 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3116 MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
3117 MSARegister lhs_msa = lhs.fp().toW();
3118 MSARegister rhs_msa = rhs.fp().toW();
3119 MSARegister scratch0 = kSimd128RegZero;
3120 MSARegister scratch1 = kSimd128ScratchReg;
3121 // If inputs are -0.0. and +0.0, then write -0.0 to scratch1.
3122 // scratch1 = (lhs == rhs) ? (lhs | rhs) : (rhs | rhs).
3123 fseq_w(scratch0, lhs_msa, rhs_msa);
3124 bsel_v(scratch0, rhs_msa, lhs_msa);
3125 or_v(scratch1, scratch0, rhs_msa);
3126 // scratch0 = isNaN(scratch1) ? scratch1: lhs.
3127 fseq_w(scratch0, scratch1, scratch1);
3128 bsel_v(scratch0, scratch1, lhs_msa);
3129 // dst = (scratch1 <= scratch0) ? scratch1 : scratch0.
3130 fsle_w(dst_msa, scratch1, scratch0);
3131 bsel_v(dst_msa, scratch0, scratch1);
3132 // Canonicalize the result.
3133 fmin_w(dst_msa, dst_msa, dst_msa);
3134}

3136void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_max(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3137 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3138 MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
3139 MSARegister lhs_msa = lhs.fp().toW();
3140 MSARegister rhs_msa = rhs.fp().toW();
3141 MSARegister scratch0 = kSimd128RegZero;
3142 MSARegister scratch1 = kSimd128ScratchReg;
3143 // If inputs are -0.0. and +0.0, then write +0.0 to scratch1.
3144 // scratch1 = (lhs == rhs) ? (lhs | rhs) : (rhs | rhs).
3145 fseq_w(scratch0, lhs_msa, rhs_msa);
3146 bsel_v(scratch0, rhs_msa, lhs_msa);
3147 and_v(scratch1, scratch0, rhs_msa);
3148 // scratch0 = isNaN(scratch1) ? scratch1: lhs.
3149 fseq_w(scratch0, scratch1, scratch1);
3150 bsel_v(scratch0, scratch1, lhs_msa);
3151 // dst = (scratch0 <= scratch1) ? scratch1 : scratch0.
3152 fsle_w(dst_msa, scratch0, scratch1);
3153 bsel_v(dst_msa, scratch0, scratch1);
3154 // Canonicalize the result.
3155 fmax_w(dst_msa, dst_msa, dst_msa);

3837
3838void LiftoffAssembler::StackCheck(Label* ool_code) {
3839 Register limit_address = kScratchReg;
3840 LoadStackLimit(limit_address, StackLimitKind::kInterruptStackLimit);
3841 Branch(ool_code, ule, sp, Operand(limit_address));
3842}
3843
3844void LiftoffAssembler::AssertUnreachable(AbortReason reason) {
3845 if (v8_flags.debug_code) Abort(reason);
3846}
3847
3848void LiftoffAssembler::PushRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
3849 LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
3850 unsigned num_gp_regs = gp_regs.GetNumRegsSet();
3851 if (num_gp_regs) {
3852 unsigned offset = num_gp_regs * kSystemPointerSize;
3853 daddiu(sp, sp, -offset);
3854 while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
3855 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
3856 offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
3857 sd(reg.gp(), MemOperand(sp, offset));
3858 gp_regs.clear(reg);
3859 }
3860 DCHECK_EQ(offset, 0);
3861 }
3862 LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
3863 unsigned num_fp_regs = fp_regs.GetNumRegsSet();
3864 if (num_fp_regs) {
3865 unsigned slot_size = IsEnabled(MIPS_SIMD) ? 16 : 8;
3866 daddiu(sp, sp, -(num_fp_regs * slot_size));
3867 unsigned offset = 0;
3868 while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
3869 LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
3870 if (IsEnabled(MIPS_SIMD)) {
3871 MacroAssembler::st_d(reg.fp().toW(), MemOperand(sp, offset));
3872 } else {
3873 MacroAssembler::Sdc1(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, offset));
3874 }
3875 fp_regs.clear(reg);
3876 offset += slot_size;
3877 }
3878 DCHECK_EQ(offset, num_fp_regs * slot_size);
3879 }
3880}
3881
3882void LiftoffAssembler::PopRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
3883 LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
3884 unsigned fp_offset = 0;
3885 while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
3886 LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
3887 if (IsEnabled(MIPS_SIMD)) {
3888 MacroAssembler::ld_d(reg.fp().toW(), MemOperand(sp, fp_offset));
3889 } else {
3890 MacroAssembler::Ldc1(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, fp_offset));
3891 }
3892 fp_regs.clear(reg);
3893 fp_offset += (IsEnabled(MIPS_SIMD) ? 16 : 8);
3894 }
3895 if (fp_offset) daddiu(sp, sp, fp_offset);
3896 LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
3897 unsigned gp_offset = 0;
3898 while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
3899 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetLastRegSet();
3900 ld(reg.gp(), MemOperand(sp, gp_offset));
3901 gp_regs.clear(reg);
3902 gp_offset += kSystemPointerSize;
3903 }
3904 daddiu(sp, sp, gp_offset);
3905}
3906
3907void LiftoffAssembler::RecordSpillsInSafepoint(
3908 SafepointTableBuilder::Safepoint& safepoint, LiftoffRegList all_spills,
3909 LiftoffRegList ref_spills, int spill_offset) {
3910 LiftoffRegList fp_spills = all_spills & kFpCacheRegList;
3911 int spill_space_size = fp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() * kSimd128Size;
3912 LiftoffRegList gp_spills = all_spills & kGpCacheRegList;
3913 while (!gp_spills.is_empty()) {
3914 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_spills.GetFirstRegSet();
3915 if (ref_spills.has(reg)) {
3916 safepoint.DefineTaggedStackSlot(spill_offset);
3917 }
3918 gp_spills.clear(reg);
3919 ++spill_offset;
3920 spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
3921 }
3922 // Record the number of additional spill slots.
3923 RecordOolSpillSpaceSize(spill_space_size);
3924}
3925
3926void LiftoffAssembler::DropStackSlotsAndRet(uint32_t num_stack_slots) {
3927 DCHECK_LT(num_stack_slots,
3928 (1 << 16) / kSystemPointerSize); // 16 bit immediate
3929 MacroAssembler::DropAndRet(static_cast<int>(num_stack_slots));
3930}
3931
3932void LiftoffAssembler::CallCWithStackBuffer(
3933 const std::initializer_list<VarState> args, const LiftoffRegister* rets,
3934 ValueKind return_kind, ValueKind out_argument_kind, int stack_bytes,
3935 ExternalReference ext_ref) {
3936 Daddu(sp, sp, -stack_bytes);
3937
3938 int arg_offset = 0;
3939 for (const VarState& arg : args) {
3940 liftoff::StoreToMemory(this, MemOperand{sp, arg_offset}, arg);
3941 arg_offset += value_kind_size(arg.kind());
3942 }
3943 DCHECK_LE(arg_offset, stack_bytes);
3944
3945 // Pass a pointer to the buffer with the arguments to the C function.
3946 // On mips, the first argument is passed in {a0}.
3947 constexpr Register kFirstArgReg = a0;
3948 mov(kFirstArgReg, sp);
3949
3950 // Now call the C function.
3951 constexpr int kNumCCallArgs = 1;
3952 PrepareCallCFunction(kNumCCallArgs, kScratchReg);
3953 CallCFunction(ext_ref, kNumCCallArgs);
3954
3955 // Move return value to the right register.
3956 const LiftoffRegister* next_result_reg = rets;
3957 if (return_kind != kVoid) {
3958 constexpr Register kReturnReg = v0;
3959#ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
3960 // When calling a host function in the simulator, if the function returns an
3961 // int32 value, the simulator does not sign-extend it to int64 because in
3962 // the simulator we do not know whether the function returns an int32 or
3963 // int64. So we need to sign extend it here.
3964 if (return_kind == kI32) {
3965 sll(next_result_reg->gp(), kReturnReg, 0);
3966 } else if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
3967 Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
3968 }
3969#else
3970 if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
3971 Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
3972 }
3973#endif
3974 ++next_result_reg;
3975 }
3976
3977 // Load potential output value from the buffer on the stack.
3978 if (out_argument_kind != kVoid) {
3979 liftoff::Load(this, *next_result_reg, MemOperand(sp, 0), out_argument_kind);
3980 }
3981
3982 Daddu(sp, sp, stack_bytes);
3983}
3984
3985void LiftoffAssembler::CallC(const std::initializer_list<VarState> args_list,
3986 ExternalReference ext_ref) {
3987 // First, prepare the stack for the C call.
3988 const int num_args = static_cast<int>(args_list.size());
3989 PrepareCallCFunction(num_args, kScratchReg);
3990
3991 // Note: If we ever need more than eight arguments we would need to load the
3992 // stack arguments to registers (via LoadToRegister), then push them to the
3993 // stack.
3994
3995 // Execute the parallel register move for register parameters.
3996 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(kCArgRegs), num_args);
3997 const VarState* const args = args_list.begin();
3998 ParallelMove parallel_move{this};
3999 for (int reg_arg = 0; reg_arg < num_args; ++reg_arg) {
4000 parallel_move.LoadIntoRegister(LiftoffRegister{kCArgRegs[reg_arg]},
4001 args[reg_arg]);
4002 }
4003 parallel_move.Execute();
4004
4005 // Now call the C function.
4006 CallCFunction(ext_ref, num_args);
4007}

4049void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst, FPURegister src,
4050 ValueKind kind) {
4051 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4052 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4053 Label not_nan;
4054 if (kind == kF32) {
4055 CompareIsNanF32(src, src);
4056 } else {
4057 DCHECK_EQ(kind, kF64);
4058 CompareIsNanF64(src, src);
4059 }
4060 BranchFalseShortF(&not_nan, USE_DELAY_SLOT);
4061 li(scratch, 1);
4062 Sw(dst, MemOperand(dst));
4063 bind(&not_nan);
4064}
4065
4066void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,
4067 LiftoffRegister src,
4068 Register tmp_gp,
4069 LiftoffRegister tmp_s128,
4070 ValueKind lane_kind) {
4071 Label not_nan;
4072 if (lane_kind == kF32) {
4073 fcun_w(tmp_s128.fp().toW(), src.fp().toW(), src.fp().toW());
4074 } else {
4075 DCHECK_EQ(lane_kind, kF64);
4076 fcun_d(tmp_s128.fp().toW(), src.fp().toW(), src.fp().toW());
4077 }
4078 BranchMSA(&not_nan, MSA_BRANCH_V, all_zero, tmp_s128.fp().toW(),
4079 USE_DELAY_SLOT);
4080 li(tmp_gp, 1);
4081 Sw(tmp_gp, MemOperand(dst));
4082 bind(&not_nan);
4083}
4084
4085void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero(Register dst) {
4086 Sd(dst, MemOperand(dst));
4087}
4088
4089void LiftoffStackSlots::Construct(int param_slots) {
4090 DCHECK_LT(0, slots_.size());
4091 SortInPushOrder();
4092 int last_stack_slot = param_slots;
4093 for (auto& slot : slots_) {
4094 const int stack_slot = slot.dst_slot_;
4095 int stack_decrement = (last_stack_slot - stack_slot) * kSystemPointerSize;
4096 DCHECK_LT(0, stack_decrement);
4097 last_stack_slot = stack_slot;
4098 const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src = slot.src_;
4099 switch (src.loc()) {
4100 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kStack:
4101 if (src.kind() != kS128) {
4102 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
4103 asm_->Ld(kScratchReg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
4104 asm_->push(kScratchReg);
4105 } else {
4106 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSimd128Size);
4107 asm_->Ld(kScratchReg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_ - 8));
4108 asm_->push(kScratchReg);
4109 asm_->Ld(kScratchReg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
4110 asm_->push(kScratchReg);
4111 }
4112 break;
4113 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kRegister: {
4114 int pushed_bytes = SlotSizeInBytes(slot);
4115 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - pushed_bytes);
4116 liftoff::push(asm_, src.reg(), src.kind());
4117 break;
4118 }
4119 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kIntConst: {
4120 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
4121 asm_->li(kScratchReg, Operand(src.i32_const()));
4122 asm_->push(kScratchReg);
4123 break;
4124 }
4125 }
4126 }
4127}
